      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Richard Aitken-Davies is a non-executive member of the Department of Transport Board.</p>

<p>Richard is an independent consultant. He has advised ministers and senior civil servants of the Department for Work and Pensions and the Ministry of Justice on the delivery of major programmes involving the procurement of services from the private and voluntary sectors.</p>

<p>Richard has had an extensive career in industry. He held senior executive roles in the Central Electricity Generating Board, Powergen, Railtrack and London & Continental Railways. His focus was on financial control, project management and organisational change.</p>

<p>Richard is a member of the Association of Chartered Certified Accountants (<abbr title="Association of Chartered Certified Accountants">ACCA</abbr>). He served on <abbr title="Association of Chartered Certified Accountants">ACCA</abbr>’s governing council and was <abbr title="Association of Chartered Certified Accountants">ACCA</abbr>’s President for the 2008 to 2009 tax year. He is also a member of the Chartered Institute of Taxation.</p>

<p>Richard also served as a non-executive director and chairman of an <abbr title="Alternative Investment Market">AIM</abbr> listed company and independent chairman of an employers’ group overseeing the administration of the Electricity Supply Pensions Scheme.</p>

</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4473">
            <h1 id="non-executive-board-member-dft">Non-executive board member, DfT</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>Non-executive board members provide the Department for Transport with strategic advice, support and challenge. They also attend departmental board meetings and meet with the management team.</p>

</div>
